    "The study suggests that a relatively shallow CNN architecture can prevent overfitting while successfully capturing the essential transformation from RGB images to the targeted spectral resolution.",
    "This approach highlights the balance between model complexity and the ability to accurately interpret and reconstruct hyperspectral data from standard RGB inputs.",
    "plifying its structure, making the neural network less complex and easier to train.",
    "EDSR achieves this by eliminating certain components, such as the batch normalization layers found in SRResNet's and the original ResNet's residual blocks.",
    "This modification not only reduces GPU memory usage but also enables the inclusion of additional residual blocks without increasing computational demands."
